text: Scirpophaga humilis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Wang, Li and Chen in 1986. It is found in China (Jiangsu, Anhui). The forewings are uniform pale yellow, females with a yellow anal tuft. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1986 Category:Schoenobiinae Category:Moths of China
title: Scirpophaga humilis
